3. HOW TO INDEPENDENTLY VERIFY EACH CLAIM

All test vectors use the exact canonical identity strings that a conformant Phase 1 implementation produces.
If you have a conformant Phase 2 implementation (available under controlled disclosure), you can run each test below and verify the expected outcome.

---

Test Vector 1 — Determinism (Claim 1)

· Input identity strings:
  ["[>",["var","x"],["int",5]]", "["<",["var","x"],["int",10]]"]
· Run Phase 2 twice with the same input. The two JSON‑serialised outputs must be byte‑identical.

Test Vector 2 — Equivalence (Claim 2)

· Input identity strings:
  ["[>",["var","x"],["int",5]]", "[">=",["var","x"],["int",6]]"]
· Expected result: The output equivalence_groups list must contain exactly one group, and that group must list both input identities as members.

Test Vector 3 — Dominance (Claim 3)

· Input identity strings:
  ["[>",["var","x"],["int",10]]", "[">",["var","x"],["int",5]]"]
· Expected result: The output dominance_removed list must contain exactly one entry, and the weaker identity x>5 must be removed from the active reduced_constraints.

Test Vector 4 — Conflict (Claim 4)

· Input identity strings:
  ["[>",["var","x"],["int",10]]", "["<",["var","x"],["int",5]]"]
· Expected result: The output status must be "CONFLICT", and the conflicts list must be non‑empty.

Test Vector 5 — Execution (Claim 5)

· Input identity string: ["[>",["var","x"],["int",5]]"]
· With execution bindings {"x": 10}: execution_result.aggregate must be True.
· With execution bindings {"x": 2}: execution_result.aggregate must be False.

Test Vector 6 — OUT_OF_SCOPE (Claim 6)

· Input identity string: ["OR",[">",["var","x"],["int",5]],["<",["var","y"],["int",10]]]
· Expected result: The output reduced_constraints must contain an entry with:
  · identity_string equal to the input string.
  · type equal to "OUT_OF_SCOPE".

Test Vector 7 — Multi‑Variable Extended Fields (Claim 7)

· Input identity string: ["">",["+",["var","x"],["var","y"]],["int",10]]
· Expected result: The output reduced_constraints must contain an entry with type: "OUT_OF_SCOPE" that also contains the fields:
  · "coeffs": {"x": 1, "y": 1}
  · "op": ">"
  · "value": 10

Test Vector 8 — Identity Ledger (Claim 8)

· Input identity strings (combine the inputs from Test Vectors 3, 6, and 7):
  ["[>",["var","x"],["int",10]]", "[">",["var","x"],["int",5]]", "["OR",[">",["var","x"],["int",5]],["<",["var","y"],["int",10]]]", "[">",["+",["var","x"],["var","y"]],["int",10]]"]
· Expected result: The output reduced_constraints list must contain exactly four entries, and every input identity string must appear exactly once.

